            <title>[LUCENE-2070] document LengthFilter wrt Unicode 4.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2070</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;LengthFilter calculates its min/max length from TermAttribute.termLength()&lt;br/&gt;
This is not characters, but instead UTF-16 code units.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my opinion this should not be changed, merely documented.&lt;br/&gt;
If we changed it, it would have an adverse performance impact because we would have to actually calculate Character.codePointCount() on the text.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you feel strongly otherwise, fixing it to count codepoints would be a trivial patch, but I&apos;d rather not hurt performance.&lt;br/&gt;
I admit I don&apos;t fully understand all the use cases for this filter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
